    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "A fully local voice assistant setup",
      "url": "https://blog.platypush.tech/article/Local-voice-assistant",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/luosjw",
      "score": 4,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "blacklight",
      "published": "2026-06-22T22:25:06Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Local voice pipelines leverage OpenAI's Whisper for Speech-to-Text and Piper for highly optimized, low-latency Text-to-Speech on consumer hardware.",
        "On-device LLM orchestration relies on Ollama or llama.cpp running quantized open models like Llama 3 8B or Mistral 7B.",
        "Integration with home automation uses Home Assistant's Wyoming protocol to stream audio from ESP32-S3 microcontrollers to local servers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "What are you doing this week?",
