      "score": 14,
      "comments": 26,
      "author": "caius",
      "published": "2026-06-22T13:11:56Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Engineers are prioritizing database schema migrations, optimizing PostgreSQL query performance, and refactoring legacy codebases for better scalability.",
        "Many are adopting Rust and Go to rewrite performance-critical microservices and build highly efficient command-line utilities.",
        "Teams are focusing on automating CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions to improve deployment safety and overall developer velocity."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Mark-of-the-web and pinning installers to sites",
      "url": "https://blog.randomoracle.io/2026/06/20/mark-of-the-web-and-pinning-installers-to-sites/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/z4vrld",
      "score": 9,
      "comments": 1,
      "author": "raymii",
      "published": "2026-06-21T05:35:25Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Windows Mark-of-the-Web (MotW) flags untrusted downloads, but attackers bypass it using container formats like ISOs, VHDs, or ZIP archives.",
        "Binding installers to specific download domains limits execution to authorized web origins, mitigating drive-by malware and phishing payloads.",
        "Harden defenses against MotW bypasses like CVE-2023-36025 by disabling the ms-appinstaller protocol and enforcing application control."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "I am dreading our LLM-written incident report future",
      "url": "https://surfingcomplexity.blog/2026/06/19/i-am-dreading-our-llm-written-incident-report-future/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/ysxvko",
      "score": 45,
      "comments": 17,
      "author": "azhenley",
      "published": "2026-06-20T00:51:33Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Delegating incident reports to LLMs bypasses critical human post-mortem analysis, erasing deep learning about complex system failures and technical debt.",
        "AI-generated RCAs risk hallucinating root causes or omitting subtle telemetry details, leading to recurring, unaddressed infrastructure vulnerabilities.",
        "Automated reports prioritize polished prose over systemic blameless post-mortem insights, hiding true architectural bottlenecks from engineering teams."
      ]
    },
